Design Frontend Developer

Blooket United States Remote

Meet the hiring team

Ben Stewart
3rd
Founder of Blooket
Job poster · LinkedIn member since 2016

About the job

About Us


Our mission at Blooket is to be the most engaging way for students to learn. That’s a pretty big goal, so we need your help!


Blooket started as a high school project and has grown to be a tool used by millions of students and teachers around the world! We specialize in creating gamified experiences that students love and empowering educators by giving them tools to create meaningful learning opportunities in and outside of their classrooms.


We’re a small team focused on building the best product we can. We like to work hard and move fast to deliver the best experience for our incredible user base. We’re looking for people who are passionate about learning and making an impact in education. As a small team, we’re extremely collaborative and we’d love to build with you!


Your Role


We want to create a sitewide experience that is easy and welcoming for our students and teachers. You’ll play a big role in making that happen. Here are some things you’ll be doing:
  • Design UI/UX for new and existing pages
  • Develop web pages using React (Next.js), Typescript, and CSS
  • Work with other developers to integrate UI with backend functionality
  • Test and optimize user interfaces
  • Conduct experiments to find optimal page layouts
  • Maintain the Blooket brand identity through fun and interesting interfaces


What We’re Looking For


We’re looking for someone who has a passion for both design and development. You’ll have to have a creative side that ensures the site looks visually pleasing, while also maintaining a good user experience and implementing it through code. To help ensure you can handle this, here are some qualifications:
  • At least 1 year in a Frontend Development focused role
  • A deep understanding of React, Next.js, Typescript, and CSS
  • An interest in testing and optimizing existing UI
  • A keen eye for details in user experience
  • Creative and design skills to develop beautiful interfaces from scratch
  • Portfolio of some relevant projects and designs
  • Decent experience with containerized environments and build tools
  • Strong knowledge of frontend technologies and passion for staying updated
  • Excellent organizational and communication skills
  • Excitement about the impact your work could have on the lives of students and teachers every day


Benefits & Compensation
  • Total compensation for this role is market competitive, including a starting base salary of $80,000- $200,000 depending on work experience, performance, and other factors evaluated during the hiring process.
  • 21 vacation days
  • Remote
  • Competitive health, dental, and vision insurance
  • Employer-sponsored 401k plan
  • Working with a small team where you can immediately see your impact
